Whereas sarcoma is a cancer of connective tissues, such as
			 nerves, muscles, joints, fat, bones, and blood vessels, and it can arise
			 anywhere in the body;

Whereas more than 13,000 people in the United States were
			 diagnosed with sarcoma last year, more than 5,000 died, and 50,000 are
			 struggling with the disease at any one time;
